Title: 14.1 Built-In Function and Operator Reference
14.13 Encryption and Compression Functions
Description: Return the length of a string before compression

Returns the length that the compressed string had before being
          compressed. Returns NULL if
          compressed_string is
          NULL.

Press CTRL+C to copy mysql> SELECT UNCOMPRESSED_LENGTH(COMPRESS(REPEAT('a',30)));
        -> 30
